\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {10}{\ignorespaces Gradient-norm adaptive loss weighting dynamics for the 5\,cm (AD5) and 6\,cm (AD6) asymmetric downstream configurations. Left panels: mean absolute gradient norms per loss component over training epochs. Right panels: corresponding adaptive weights computed via the EMA-smoothed rebalancing scheme. In both configurations, the physics loss gradient norm (orange) starts approximately two orders of magnitude above the WSS reference (blue) and is progressively down-weighted. The WSS weight remains anchored at 1.0 as the reference term.}}{22}{figure.caption.12}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:adaptive_weights}{{10}{22}{Gradient-norm adaptive loss weighting dynamics for the 5\,cm (AD5) and 6\,cm (AD6) asymmetric downstream configurations. Left panels: mean absolute gradient norms per loss component over training epochs. Right panels: corresponding adaptive weights computed via the EMA-smoothed rebalancing scheme. In both configurations, the physics loss gradient norm (orange) starts approximately two orders of magnitude above the WSS reference (blue) and is progressively down-weighted. The WSS weight remains anchored at 1.0 as the reference term}{figure.caption.12}{}}
